column5: Ah yes another annual Christmas day ice fishin' trip is in the books. The weather was frightful but the pikes were so delightful!!! No giants but we did catch a bunch with 2 really decent sized ones plus we lost a couple of really good ones. Ice thickness.............15" of good black ice. I'll let the pictures tell the story. Enjoy!!
Nice!  I was in Collingwood for Christmas.  There was people fishing from shore....
Sweet pike Dave. Looks like you are continuing to shrink away. How much weight have you lost now?
Good stuff Dave. Nice pike! It's getting cold here finally...
I would take those pike any day through the ice
